summary: "very few documented health issues with ‘delayed’ or completely prevented evolution" is not the same as "No documented health...
question: "very few documented health issues with ‘delayed’ or completely prevented evolution" is not the same as "No documented health issues." can you elaborate?
answer:
Ah yes, I could have been more specific.

What I should have said is that there are no documented cases of physical health issues that developed in a Pokémon explicitly because of delayed evolution. There are rare cases where issues arise, but that is because of either pre-existing conditions or exposure to some kind of disease, the effects of which are exacerbated by delayed evolution.

On its own, putting off evolution in a Pokémon is not dangerous, but there are a few other factors to look into for absolute certainty.

And again, I’m no psychologist; I can’t speak to the emotional/mental developmental impacts quite as much.

-Thea

title: Meltan Research Update: Introducing Melmetal!
excerpt: The Meltan research continues with Professors Oak and Willow, who appear to have discovered an Evolution—the first of its kind! What could this mean? Here’s ...
description:
The First Mythical Pokemon to Evolve!

Everyone has been talking about the new mythical pokemon Meltan. As more information comes out about this mysterious pokemon in Pokemon Let’s Go Evee/Pickachu, Nintendo reveals that Meltan can evolve into Melmetal! There are so many questions that pokemon lovers gave for this new mythical pokemon! Pokemon Let’s Go is set to release November 16,2018! For now, let’s enjoy catching pokemon in our backyard with Pokemon Go or with your 3ds with Pokemon Ultra Sun and Ultra Moon!

blog.name: pokegodsandmissingno
blog.title: P̵o̵K̸é̴G̸o̸D̷s̸ and Frightful Things to Come?
blog.description: There is a growing desire and expectation of humans here on Earth in making full contact with PoKéMoN who are still unknown. Back in 1995, when I saw my first UPM (Unindexed Pocket Monster), I found out very quickly that other people thought you were totally crazy if you said you saw such things. The world has changed quite a bit since then when I was a child. In fact, in late 1997, a poll taken in Kanto shows that for the first time ever, more than fifty percent of residents now believe in PokéGODS's. Since then, there have been polls that put the figure at over eighty percent or more.
